<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Courteous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Courteous,</orth> 1) polite, civil: <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 9, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.148" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 76</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.111" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 5, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.57" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.6.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 6, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 3, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 227</bibl>. Followed by <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 167</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 30</bibl>.<lb />2) kind, benevolent: <cit><quote>thanks, c. wall,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 179</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your c. pains,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.412" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 412</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an affable and c. gentleman,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 98</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>do me this c. office,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 278</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my c. lord,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.185" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 185</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O c. Tybalt!</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 62</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>